# fit and plot func_elip_gauss

from scipy.optimize import curve_fit

u = uvw_this_scan_goodvis[0]
v = uvw_this_scan_goodvis[1]
stokes_I_amp = np.abs(stokes_I_this_scan_goodvis)
phase_angle = np.angle(stokes_I_this_scan_goodvis)

weight_this_scan = uv_sourcemodel.uv_tapper_weight(uvw_this_scan_goodvis, 0.3)
popt, pcov = curve_fit(uv_sourcemodel.func_elip_gauss, (u, v), stokes_I_amp,
 p0=[1/np.max(u)/2,1/np.max(v)/2,0,np.max(stokes_I_amp)],sigma = 1/weight_this_scan**2)

popt_phase, pcov_phase = curve_fit(uv_sourcemodel.func_phase_sin, 
    (u, v), (np.sin(phase_angle)),sigma = 1/weight_this_scan**2,  p0=[0,0], absolute_sigma=True)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(10,5))
ax = ax.ravel()
ax[0].scatter(u, v, c=stokes_I_amp, s=10)

uu = np.linspace(np.min(u), np.max(u), 100)
vv = np.linspace(np.min(v), np.max(v), 100)
U, V = np.meshgrid(uu, vv)
Z = uv_sourcemodel.func_elip_gauss((U,V), *popt)
ax[0].contourf(U, V, Z)
ax[0].scatter(u, v, c=stokes_I_amp, s=10)

Zp = uv_sourcemodel.func_phase_sin((U,V), *popt_phase)
ax[1].contourf(U, V, Zp, cmap='inferno')
ax[1].scatter(u, v, c=np.sin(phase_angle), s=10, cmap='inferno')

# convert the analytic guassian in uv space to image space


sigma_x = popt[0]
sigma_y = popt[1]
theta = -popt[2]
amp = popt[3]

l0, m0 = popt_phase

alpha_0, delta_0 = ref_proc

alpha_rad, delta_rad = uv_sourcemodel.lm_to_radec(l0, m0, alpha_0, delta_0)

def func_gauss_xy(x, y, x0, y0, sigma_x, sigma_y, theta, amp):
    xx = x - x0
    yy = y - y0
    return amp/(4*np.pi**2 *sigma_x*sigma_y) * np.exp(
        -0.5 * (xx*np.cos(theta) - yy*np.sin(theta))**2 / sigma_x**2 
        -0.5 * (xx*np.sin(theta) + yy*np.cos(theta))**2 / sigma_y**2)

x = np.linspace(-.015+alpha_0, .015+alpha_0, 300)
y = np.linspace(-.015+delta_0, .015+delta_0, 300)


X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
Z = func_gauss_xy(X, Y, alpha_rad, delta_rad, sigma_x, sigma_y, theta, amp)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize=(5,5))
ax.contourf(X, Y, Z, cmap='gray_r', origin='lower')
ax.set_xlim(alpha_0+.015, alpha_0-.015)
ax.set_aspect('equal', 'box')

r_sun_rad  = 959.63 / 3600 * np.pi/180
ax.plot(alpha_0 + r_sun_rad * np.cos(np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 100)), delta_0 + r_sun_rad * np.sin(np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 100)), color='red')

ax.plot(alpha_0, delta_0, '+', color='red')
ax.set_xlabel('RA (rad)')
ax.set_ylabel('DEC (rad)')

# compare with interferometer image

f_fits = './peijin_one_time-image.fits'
import astropy.io.fits as fits
from astropy.wcs import WCS

# read fits file
hdulist = fits.open(f_fits)
image = hdulist[0].data.squeeze()

# get coordinate from the fits file
wcs = WCS(hdulist[0].header, naxis=2)

hdulist.close()



# plot the image
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize=(5,5), subplot_kw={'projection': wcs})
ax.imshow(image, cmap='gray', origin='lower')
# mark CRPIX of wcs in the image
ax.plot(wcs.wcs.crpix[0], wcs.wcs.crpix[1], '+', color='r')

ax.set_xlim(image.shape[1]//2-60, image.shape[1]//2+60)
ax.set_ylim(image.shape[0]//2-60, image.shape[0]//2+60)

ax.grid(color='white', ls='dotted')
#ax.plot(SkyCoord(ra=alpha_rad*180/np.pi, dec=delta_rad*180/np.pi, unit='deg'), color='g')


r_sun_rad  = 959.63 / 3600 * np.pi/180
ax.plot((alpha_0 + r_sun_rad * np.cos(np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 100)))*180/np.pi, 
        (delta_0 + r_sun_rad * np.sin(np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 100)))*180/np.pi,
          color='red',transform=ax.get_transform('world'))
